  "exec_summary": "The European Securities and Markets Authority has launched a consultation to reduce the business burden of regulatory requirements, aiming to simplify and streamline processes for firms. In Belgium and the broader EU, the Markets in Crypto-Assets regulation remains a key focus, with the European Commission considering amendments to MiCA to extend its scope to non-EU stablecoin issuers. The National Bank of Belgium and the Financial Services and Markets Authority are likely to play a crucial role in implementing and enforcing MiCA in the Belgian market. Meanwhile, the European Union's Anti-Money Laundering framework continues to be enforced, with authorities such as the European Banking Authority monitoring and supervising firms to prevent financial crime.",
